We live together in the same shack every day, so what's there to miss?

277
00:18:49,880 --> 00:18:51,300
I don't want to be your longing.

278
00:18:51,600 --> 00:18:52,880
How can I not miss you?

279
00:18:54,040 --> 00:19:04,120
I see you staring at the Boss every day until your eyes pop out like a toad's. Just thinking about you breaks my heart.

280
00:19:05,620 --> 00:19:06,660
I'm a person too.

281
00:19:07,960 --> 00:19:11,420
Once in a while, for a change of pace, look at me too.

282
00:19:12,280 --> 00:19:12,800
You fool.

283
00:19:13,800 --> 00:19:17,760
I can live without eating, but I can't live a single day without thinking about the Boss.

284
00:19:19,780 --> 00:19:21,880
If the Boss marries another woman...

285
00:19:22,980 --> 00:19:23,940
Do you think I'll just stand by?

286
00:19:24,280 --> 00:19:25,980
I'll kill those women, kill the Boss, and then kill myself.

287
00:19:34,530 --> 00:19:39,270
Even if you marry another man, I can't kill you.

288
00:19:40,570 --> 00:19:44,170
How could I kill someone as fragile as a blade of grass?

289
00:19:46,690 --> 00:19:49,490
It's better for me to die alone.

290
00:20:17,810 --> 00:20:20,610
Police, police, police... what, are you looking for the police?

291
00:20:22,590 --> 00:20:23,390
What about the examination hall?

292
00:20:23,470 --> 00:20:23,810
How is it?

293
00:20:23,810 --> 00:20:24,950
I went out, I went out, I went out.

294
00:20:24,970 --> 00:20:25,750
I don't know, I don't know.

295
00:20:26,070 --> 00:20:29,230
But Boss, this isn't a safe place.

296
00:20:31,730 --> 00:20:33,650
Hey, this looks really delicious.

297
00:20:42,130 --> 00:20:43,130
Welcome.

298
00:20:44,090 --> 00:20:44,710
Are you Yoomyungdo?

299
00:20:46,850 --> 00:20:47,590
Yes, that's right.

300
00:20:47,850 --> 00:20:48,170
Follow me.

301
00:20:48,830 --> 00:20:50,870
No, I need to know what's going on before I can go.

302
00:20:53,370 --> 00:20:54,490
Hey, what's wrong?

303
00:20:54,710 --> 00:20:55,230
Sir.

304
00:20:55,850 --> 00:20:56,870
Just watch the store.

305
00:20:57,010 --> 00:20:57,970
Get that rope, you bastard.

306
00:20:58,350 --> 00:20:59,710
No, so...

307
00:21:00,570 --> 00:21:01,750
Did you sell a lot?

308
00:21:04,330 --> 00:21:04,890
What?

309
00:21:09,210 --> 00:21:12,010
Didn't I tell you to just go on your own and not follow me?

310
00:21:25,580 --> 00:21:29,860
There's a gisaeng who saw you two come in together, yet you keep playing dumb.

311
00:21:30,800 --> 00:21:34,740
Just a guy you met on the street and had a drink with? Who is he and what does he do?

312
00:21:35,740 --> 00:21:38,320
Even if you're close, if you don't know, you don't know.

313
00:21:38,380 --> 00:21:40,100
I get that you didn't see him and don't know him.

314
00:21:40,900 --> 00:21:41,740
Hey, tell me.

315
00:21:42,580 --> 00:21:43,660
Who is he and what does he do?

316
00:21:45,520 --> 00:21:46,900
You have to untie him to make him talk.

317
00:21:48,280 --> 00:21:48,880
Tell me.

318
00:21:50,640 --> 00:21:51,780
I am...

319
00:21:56,040 --> 00:21:56,960
Fine.

320
00:21:59,280 --> 00:22:00,920
Is the teacher outside?

321
00:22:02,180 --> 00:22:02,420
Teacher.

322
00:22:51,130 --> 00:22:51,810
Why?

323
00:23:01,050 --> 00:23:01,730
Sir.

324
00:23:03,230 --> 00:23:08,750
I don't know anything, but I'm innocent.

325
00:23:09,530 --> 00:23:13,050
My only crime is working hard to make a living.

326
00:23:13,250 --> 00:23:15,290
But why are you doing this?

327
00:23:18,850 --> 00:23:21,770
I pay my taxes well.

328
00:23:21,770 --> 00:23:25,130
I'm good to the police and I'm a first-class citizen of the Japanese Empire.

329
00:23:59,680 --> 00:24:01,300
I have something to tell you.

330
00:24:01,480 --> 00:24:02,660
So cooperate.

331
00:24:03,140 --> 00:24:03,800
Who is that guy?

332
00:24:04,120 --> 00:24:05,420
I don't even know who he is.

333
00:24:05,720 --> 00:24:08,060
I told you, he's just some beggar I met on the street.

334
00:24:09,380 --> 00:24:09,520
A beggar?

335
00:24:10,640 --> 00:24:11,320
That guy is a beggar?

336
00:24:12,260 --> 00:24:15,820
I'm not saying he's really a beggar, I'm saying his clothes are like a beggar's.

337
00:24:16,660 --> 00:24:16,940
That's right.

338
00:24:17,360 --> 00:24:19,660
His clothes are like a beggar's and he looks like a beggar.

339
00:24:19,860 --> 00:24:20,960
Tell me clearly.

340
00:24:20,980 --> 00:24:22,140
Is that guy a beggar or not?

341
00:24:22,360 --> 00:24:23,120
I'm telling you the truth.

342
00:24:23,460 --> 00:24:24,940
I'm telling you, he's a real beggar.

343
00:24:25,260 --> 00:24:27,200
I'm telling you, I only know how to make money.

344
00:24:27,340 --> 00:24:29,300
Ask the beggars at Yeomcheon Bridge about him.

345
00:24:29,360 --> 00:24:29,800
Jeong-don.

346
00:24:29,940 --> 00:24:30,160
Sir.

347
00:24:33,760 --> 00:24:35,040
That guy from Yeomcheon Bridge?

348
00:24:35,880 --> 00:24:36,040
Yes.

349
00:24:36,640 --> 00:24:37,440
It seems certain.

350
00:24:39,840 --> 00:24:41,260
You've been through a lot.

351
00:24:43,180 --> 00:24:48,480
I was already having a headache because of the Sung Min-jae escape incident, and now this has made things very difficult.

352
00:24:49,700 --> 00:24:52,220
The situation is very bad, isn't it?

353
00:24:52,280 --> 00:24:52,660
Good.

354
00:24:52,740 --> 00:24:53,080
Good.

355
00:24:53,120 --> 00:24:56,180
When things get this complicated, you're bound to meet in one place.

356
00:24:56,720 --> 00:24:59,560
Somehow, this incident is definitely related to the attempted assassination of Superintendent Endo.

357
00:24:59,620 --> 00:25:00,360
I have a feeling.

358
00:25:00,360 --> 00:25:00,900
No, then...

359
00:25:00,900 --> 00:25:01,160
No.

360
00:25:01,300 --> 00:25:01,360
No.

361
00:25:01,400 --> 00:25:02,000
Don't ask why.

362
00:25:02,040 --> 00:25:02,860
I don't know either.

363
00:25:04,740 --> 00:25:05,520
Where is the teacher?

364
00:25:05,660 --> 00:25:05,860
Sir.

365
00:25:08,620 --> 00:25:09,840
Singers are connected to each other.

366
00:25:09,860 --> 00:25:12,020
If you dig deep enough, you'll find what you're looking for.

367
00:25:12,480 --> 00:25:13,500
What should we do with that guy?

368
00:25:13,580 --> 00:25:13,900
Let him go.

369
00:25:13,960 --> 00:25:15,140
He's said what he needs to say.

370
00:25:15,480 --> 00:25:16,000
Put a tail on him.

371
00:25:16,300 --> 00:25:17,300
I'll tail him myself...

372
00:25:17,300 --> 00:25:18,400
Sir.

373
00:25:18,520 --> 00:25:18,840
Sir.

374
00:25:24,660 --> 00:25:25,940
Hey, you punk.

375
00:25:26,040 --> 00:25:27,180
Is that girl that great?

376
00:25:28,220 --> 00:25:32,120
A woman is medicine if you like her in moderation, but she's poison if you fall too hard.

377
00:25:33,520 --> 00:25:34,420
You stupid fool.

378
00:25:35,060 --> 00:25:35,940
You're going to ruin your life.

379
00:25:37,360 --> 00:25:39,420
Do you have any hammers in your shop?

380
00:25:39,860 --> 00:25:41,140
You'd have to go to a hardware store for that.

381
00:25:42,200 --> 00:25:43,020
Get me one.

382
00:25:43,360 --> 00:25:43,740
What for?

383
00:25:45,100 --> 00:25:46,740
To nail your mouth shut.

384
00:25:46,740 --> 00:25:49,440
You're a man, but you get scared by a little threat like that.

385
00:25:49,780 --> 00:25:52,200
It's not that I wanted to tell him, it just came out...

386
00:25:52,200 --> 00:25:53,000
What do you mean, you didn't know?

387
00:25:53,080 --> 00:25:53,860
You're the one who told him everything.

388
00:25:54,200 --> 00:25:56,480
Even if I hadn't told him, they would have found out soon enough.

389
00:25:56,680 --> 00:25:59,880
Even so, is it the same as them finding out from somewhere else?

390
00:26:00,180 --> 00:26:00,840
You're his friend.

391
00:26:02,240 --> 00:26:02,840
Friend?

392
00:26:04,040 --> 00:26:08,080
I can pretend to die for a friend, but I can't actually die.

393
00:26:09,340 --> 00:26:12,980
If you can't actually die, then friend or not, it's nothing.

394
00:26:14,980 --> 00:26:16,060
I can't do it.

395
00:26:17,080 --> 00:26:20,720
If I had two or three lives, maybe, but I only have one.

396
00:26:20,840 --> 00:26:21,540
I can't do it.

397
00:26:22,260 --> 00:26:22,860
Right.

398
00:26:23,800 --> 00:26:26,560
Then cherish your one and only life.

399
00:26:26,960 --> 00:26:27,860
Before someone takes it from you.

400
00:26:29,640 --> 00:26:30,780
Hey, you bastard!

401
00:26:30,800 --> 00:26:31,860
Aren't you going too far?

402
00:26:32,200 --> 00:26:32,560
That's enough!

403
00:26:32,640 --> 00:26:33,360
Find Jun-seo!

404
00:26:33,940 --> 00:26:35,840
We have to find him before the police do!

405
00:26:36,360 --> 00:26:38,320
We have to find him quickly and send him to some remote place.

406
00:26:38,480 --> 00:26:40,520
We can't let him spend his youth in prison.

407
00:26:41,120 --> 00:26:42,220
You beggar-like bastard!

408
00:26:42,220 --> 00:26:42,660
Oh my!

409
00:26:47,220 --> 00:26:49,260
I told you, Han-young.

410
00:26:52,560 --> 00:26:56,640
Love was supposed to make us stronger.

411
00:26:59,660 --> 00:27:02,820
But I guess that's not it.

412
00:27:05,380 --> 00:27:12,120
I thought so when we were together.

413
00:27:15,800 --> 00:27:22,500
But now that I'm alone, I feel myself getting weaker.

414
00:27:23,240 --> 00:27:24,440
I'm sorry.

415
00:27:25,840 --> 00:27:27,380
I ran away by myself, didn't I?

416
00:27:29,320 --> 00:27:30,400
No, Han-young.

417
00:27:31,960 --> 00:27:35,440
That's not what I meant...

418
00:27:35,780 --> 00:27:37,940
That will never happen.

419
00:27:39,340 --> 00:27:40,400
We'll always be together.

420
00:27:44,340 --> 00:27:45,780
In life and in death.

421
00:27:52,480 --> 00:27:53,200
Hey!

422
00:27:54,480 --> 00:27:55,620
Aren't you guys worried?

423
00:27:55,960 --> 00:28:00,960
You don't even know if the Boss who saved your lives is dead or alive, and you're just sitting here holding hands and chatting?

424
00:28:02,600 --> 00:28:06,160
How do you know so well what men and women do when they meet?

425
00:28:06,780 --> 00:28:08,160
I guess you're a woman too, sis.

426
00:28:08,260 --> 00:28:09,040
Seeing you get jealous.

427
00:28:09,180 --> 00:28:09,900
Shut up!

428
00:28:10,000 --> 00:28:11,560
Wait, what happened?

429
00:28:12,160 --> 00:28:14,460
Didn't he get caught by a robber, beaten up, and die?

430
00:28:14,460 --> 00:28:16,100
Have you ever seen a robber do that?

431
00:28:16,260 --> 00:28:18,440
When it's dark, you can't tell if it's a beggar or something else.

432
00:28:18,740 --> 00:28:19,600
Don't be ridiculous.

433
00:28:19,920 --> 00:28:21,100
He'd get robbed trying to rob the Boss.

434
00:28:21,480 --> 00:28:22,480
He'd die, he'd die.

435
00:28:22,920 --> 00:28:22,920
Hey!

436
00:28:23,620 --> 00:28:24,700
They're here again.

437
00:28:26,500 --> 00:28:28,140
Is your leader in there?

438
00:28:28,640 --> 00:28:28,900
He's not here.

439
00:28:29,060 --> 00:28:29,360
Yes.

440
00:28:30,620 --> 00:28:31,700
He's really not here.

441
00:28:32,040 --> 00:28:33,660
We've been looking for him all night.

442
00:28:33,880 --> 00:28:34,500
All night.

443
00:28:38,260 --> 00:28:40,000
There's only bedbugs and rat droppings here.

444
00:28:40,100 --> 00:28:40,660
There's nothing here.

445
00:29:08,270 --> 00:29:09,910
Our bean paste...

446
00:29:11,570 --> 00:29:12,610
No meat either?

447
00:29:12,850 --> 00:29:12,970
No.

448
00:29:15,150 --> 00:29:15,970
There's nothing.

449
00:29:17,650 --> 00:29:19,030
Did you search everywhere?

450
00:29:19,410 --> 00:29:19,550
Yes.

451
00:29:19,910 --> 00:29:21,420
I've searched everywhere, even the bean paste pot...

452
00:29:29,040 --> 00:29:32,340
You really don't know where your leader is?

453
00:29:34,140 --> 00:29:34,960
That's right.

454
00:29:36,040 --> 00:29:37,540
We really don't know right now.

455
00:29:38,280 --> 00:29:39,540
Don't say you don't know even if you do.

456
00:29:39,600 --> 00:29:40,500
Who do you think I am?

457
00:29:40,500 --> 00:29:42,460
You'll have to search the bean paste pot carefully.

458
00:29:42,540 --> 00:29:43,340
If you're so pure...

459
00:29:48,290 --> 00:29:49,790
Bring those two.

460
00:29:49,890 --> 00:29:49,970
Yes.

461
00:29:51,790 --> 00:29:52,530
No!

462
00:29:52,970 --> 00:29:53,470
No!

463
00:29:53,970 --> 00:29:54,370
Let go!

464
00:29:58,170 --> 00:29:58,970
Let go!

465
00:29:59,590 --> 00:29:59,590
Let go!

466
00:29:59,610 --> 00:29:59,970
Let go!

467
00:30:00,150 --> 00:30:00,630
Let go!

468
00:30:00,630 --> 00:30:00,830
Let go!

469
00:30:01,490 --> 00:30:01,710
Let go!

470
00:30:01,730 --> 00:30:01,730
Let go!

471
00:30:01,970 --> 00:30:01,970
Let go!

472
00:30:02,370 --> 00:30:02,770
Let go!

473
00:30:02,830 --> 00:30:03,330
Let go!

474
00:30:03,430 --> 00:30:03,710
Let go!

475
00:30:03,890 --> 00:30:04,150
Let go!

476
00:30:06,490 --> 00:30:07,290
Let go!

477
00:30:07,290 --> 00:30:08,090
Let go!

478
00:30:08,090 --> 00:30:08,430
Let go!

479
00:30:08,430 --> 00:30:09,010
Let go!

480
00:30:23,360 --> 00:30:24,160
Let go!

481
00:30:24,160 --> 00:30:24,620
Do-yeon.

482
00:30:26,560 --> 00:30:27,360
Do-yeon.

483
00:30:27,700 --> 00:30:28,100
Hama.

484
00:30:32,240 --> 00:30:33,040
Gan-hee.

485
00:30:33,400 --> 00:30:33,840
Do-yeon.

486
00:30:34,140 --> 00:30:35,560
How did you know there was a doggy door here?

487
00:30:37,400 --> 00:30:37,800
Min-jae.

488
00:30:38,240 --> 00:30:38,840
Min-jae.

489
00:30:39,980 --> 00:30:40,720
Hey, Hama, this is bad.

490
00:30:41,340 --> 00:30:42,720
Can you get a rickshaw?

491
00:31:37,700 --> 00:31:40,420
Violence is not something to be used on people.

492
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:43,540
How much it must have hurt.

493
00:31:45,840 --> 00:31:50,100
Even after being hurt like this, are you still not going to tell me where your Boss is?

494
00:31:51,600 --> 00:31:52,940
We don't know.

495
00:31:54,460 --> 00:31:56,420
How can we tell you what we don't know?

496
00:31:56,660 --> 00:31:58,760
If you knew, you would have told me already.

497
00:31:59,400 --> 00:32:00,260
It's true.

498
00:32:00,700 --> 00:32:02,960
I really hate violence, but...

499
00:32:04,500 --> 00:32:06,640
When this is the only way, there's no other choice.

500
00:32:08,240 --> 00:32:09,120
Excuse me.

501
00:32:10,320 --> 00:32:12,340
We might die anyway.

502
00:32:12,500 --> 00:32:13,840
What kind of teacher is that?

503
00:32:14,620 --> 00:32:19,860
Unlike others, we haven't lost our teeth, so our jaw muscles are weak.

504
00:32:20,180 --> 00:32:20,600
Sir.

505
00:32:21,460 --> 00:32:21,680
Yes.

506
00:33:12,800 --> 00:33:16,400
Just being pretty and knowing how to pour drinks doesn't make you a gisaeng.

507
00:33:18,480 --> 00:33:24,700
You have to smile in front of a customer who wants to laugh, and you have to cry in front of a customer who wants to see tears.

508
00:33:26,080 --> 00:33:30,080
How dare you be rude to a customer you don't like?

509
00:33:32,300 --> 00:33:34,520
Do you know the difference between a woman and a gisaeng?

510
00:33:36,000 --> 00:33:43,960
A woman must be a person before she is a woman, and a gisaeng must be a woman before she is a person.

511
00:33:45,540 --> 00:33:50,560
While you're a gisaeng, you have to throw away all the pride that ordinary people have.

512
00:33:53,820 --> 00:34:00,720
There's a girl among you who, because of her pride, refuses to lower herself in front of men.

513
00:34:03,340 --> 00:34:10,480
Keep that nature well hidden, and take it out again when you quit being a gisaeng and go back to being a woman.

514
00:34:14,480 --> 00:34:16,180
Everyone, leave. Haewol, you stay.

515
00:34:34,710 --> 00:34:38,390
You said you'd only be a gisaeng until you're twenty-two, right?

516
00:34:39,490 --> 00:34:40,410
Yes.

517
00:34:41,450 --> 00:34:41,670
Why?

518
00:34:43,530 --> 00:34:50,870
By then, my younger siblings will be able to take care of themselves, and after that, I want to live for myself.

519
00:34:52,850 --> 00:34:57,730
You're a very smart girl to be planning your life at such a young age.

520
00:35:01,350 --> 00:35:08,450
But your plan requires you to earn a lot of money in a short period of time...

521
00:35:08,450 --> 00:35:11,890
What will happen if every customer who sees you turns their back on you?

522
00:35:13,670 --> 00:35:15,110
What are you talking about?

523
00:35:16,350 --> 00:35:18,190
I'm talking about Director Ikeda.

524
00:35:19,310 --> 00:35:21,750
You haven't even visited him once, have you?

525
00:35:23,910 --> 00:35:27,210
You know that Director Ikeda is the Governor-General's nephew, right?

526
00:35:28,910 --> 00:35:33,510
From now on, the people from the Governor-General's office won't be pleased with you.

527
00:35:33,810 --> 00:35:34,530
I don't care.

528
00:35:35,250 --> 00:35:36,590
I'm not pleased with him either.

529
00:35:36,770 --> 00:35:40,890
It's a crude expression, but there's a difference between scary and dirty.

530
00:35:42,690 --> 00:35:49,370
Even if I starve to death and my family ends up on the street, I can't go visit that man.

531
00:35:51,590 --> 00:35:53,770
Madam, someone's here to see you.

532
00:35:57,210 --> 00:35:58,570
You can't come in here.

533
00:35:59,790 --> 00:36:02,210
Madam, that person just came in without thinking...

534
00:36:22,770 --> 00:36:23,530
No.

535
00:36:24,690 --> 00:36:29,130
This will be the first and last time I ask or demand anything of you.

536
00:36:30,350 --> 00:36:31,470
I won't do this again.

537
00:36:33,070 --> 00:36:34,270
Don't say that.

538
00:36:35,610 --> 00:36:36,770
It's been so long.

539
00:36:38,570 --> 00:36:41,150
I'm so happy that you came to see me.

540
00:36:42,490 --> 00:36:43,250
Really?

541
00:36:43,250 --> 00:36:49,270
I was so surprised when I heard you ran away from home.

542
00:36:50,150 --> 00:36:53,350
From the person who left her eight-year-old child in that house and walked away?

543
00:36:53,890 --> 00:36:55,550
That was all for you...

544
00:36:55,550 --> 00:36:56,490
It was for me, wasn't it?

545
00:36:57,570 --> 00:37:07,210
There was no thought for you, who lived as you pleased after leaving me behind. It was all for your young son from beginning to end, right?

546
00:37:08,150 --> 00:37:10,530
