551
00:37:27,650 --> 00:37:29,330
This mother has spent her whole life...

552
00:37:29,330 --> 00:37:30,530
I don't plan on staying long.

553
00:37:32,070 --> 00:37:36,970
As soon as I get a message from Shanghai and Min-jae's body has recovered enough, I'll take him away immediately.

554
00:37:39,350 --> 00:37:41,090
Don't worry.

555
00:37:42,030 --> 00:37:44,590
I'll take care of him with all my strength.

556
00:37:46,210 --> 00:37:47,350
He's precious to me.

557
00:37:48,630 --> 00:37:55,670
He's a comrade, a teacher, and like a mother to me. He's a very precious person, more than you can imagine.

558
00:37:57,850 --> 00:37:58,490
Han-young.

559
00:38:00,630 --> 00:38:01,590
Han-young.

560
00:38:03,230 --> 00:38:05,530
Can't you call me 'mother' just once?

561
00:38:06,710 --> 00:38:16,030
When you sold me to the Lee family of Samcheong-dong 14 years ago, my mother died.

562
00:38:45,130 --> 00:38:46,730
Go out first.

563
00:38:47,090 --> 00:38:47,250
Yes.

564
00:38:49,350 --> 00:38:51,910
The madam told me to give you this.

565
00:39:05,250 --> 00:39:06,930
I'm only taking 300 won.

566
00:39:07,610 --> 00:39:08,290
Please return the rest.

567
00:39:10,470 --> 00:39:11,530
Um...

568
00:39:13,110 --> 00:39:15,710
Do you know where Chunsam is right now?

569
00:39:17,750 --> 00:39:18,810
Chunsam...

570
00:39:18,810 --> 00:39:19,590
You know the Boss?

571
00:39:22,190 --> 00:39:27,290
Then maybe the one who gave the Boss the Yi Sang poetry collection...

572
00:39:29,150 --> 00:39:30,150
Yes...

573
00:39:31,290 --> 00:39:33,170
Could I possibly meet him?

574
00:39:35,030 --> 00:39:39,050
Everyone at the shack is worried, but we don't have any news.

575
00:39:41,230 --> 00:39:41,990
What should I do?

576
00:39:42,430 --> 00:39:43,750
He's badly hurt.

577
00:39:44,550 --> 00:39:47,390
He won't be safe if he's caught by the patrolmen.

578
00:39:48,290 --> 00:39:49,170
Don't worry too much.

579
00:39:49,850 --> 00:39:52,630
The Boss is not someone who will go down easily.

580
00:40:02,620 --> 00:40:05,340
How can two women be so different?

581
00:40:05,340 --> 00:40:11,340
Just as there are different sizes of loaches, from as big as an adult's finger to tiny ones, I guess all women are the same.

582
00:40:12,780 --> 00:40:17,420
I'm sure my eyes are covered not with pollack skin, but with something thicker, like pig skin.

583
00:40:17,940 --> 00:40:20,960
What should I do? I find Crow a thousand times prettier than that woman.

584
00:40:21,360 --> 00:40:23,260
That's what happens when you like someone.

585
00:40:24,520 --> 00:40:26,800
This is a hospital where one of two has to die to be cured.

586
00:40:28,760 --> 00:40:29,480
Crow...

587
00:40:40,350 --> 00:40:41,350
Yes.

588
00:40:42,670 --> 00:40:43,950
You've been through a lot of trouble.

589
00:40:45,150 --> 00:40:45,510
Not at all.

590
00:40:48,410 --> 00:40:51,110
There are always a lot of people behind me.

591
00:40:52,250 --> 00:40:54,530
Many women, many men.

592
00:40:55,750 --> 00:40:58,770
But there are very few people I can ask for help.

593
00:41:00,950 --> 00:41:08,390
People are the most precious thing to people, but it's all because I lack virtue.

594
00:41:10,610 --> 00:41:13,190
Just tell me what I can do.

595
00:41:14,070 --> 00:41:15,510
I'll help in any way I can.

596
00:41:17,870 --> 00:41:20,330
Even if I suspect something, I won't tell anyone.

597
00:41:20,850 --> 00:41:21,950
Don't worry.

598
00:41:33,880 --> 00:41:34,880
I'm sorry.

599
00:41:38,200 --> 00:41:39,200
Who are you?

600
00:41:39,820 --> 00:41:40,520
Don't worry.

601
00:41:41,940 --> 00:41:43,260
Han-young...

602
00:41:43,720 --> 00:41:45,380
He went back to Yeomcheon Bridge.

603
00:41:45,960 --> 00:41:47,720
He'll be safe there, so don't worry too much.

604
00:41:49,280 --> 00:41:50,280
Where am I?

605
00:41:53,300 --> 00:41:55,500
You should have some porridge...

606
00:41:56,280 --> 00:41:58,520
What kind of place is this?

607
00:42:03,030 --> 00:42:03,510
It's a gisaeng house.

608
00:42:04,370 --> 00:42:06,290
And I'm a gisaeng who works in this house.

609
00:42:09,860 --> 00:42:11,640
Everyone has their own way of living.

610
00:42:12,320 --> 00:42:15,760
A noble lady, a servant girl, or a gisaeng...

611
00:42:17,780 --> 00:42:24,180
Like it or not, I think it's better to sing and dance than to be dragged away as a comfort woman.

612
00:42:26,800 --> 00:42:30,880
Am I making things difficult for you by asking unnecessary questions?

613
00:42:31,680 --> 00:42:32,000
No.

614
00:42:33,660 --> 00:42:35,190
Actually, I'm envious.

615
00:42:37,040 --> 00:42:43,060
To dedicate your life to something more precious than just making a living, and also...

616
00:42:44,900 --> 00:42:45,520
Pardon?

617
00:42:48,020 --> 00:42:52,320
I'm envious that you can do the same work as the person you love.

618
00:42:54,200 --> 00:42:57,140
How do you know Han-young?

619
00:42:58,720 --> 00:43:00,520
I know someone at Yeomcheon Church.

620
00:43:01,780 --> 00:43:02,480
Yeomcheon Church?

621
00:43:03,800 --> 00:43:04,680
Yes.

622
00:43:07,040 --> 00:43:08,680
Someone you like?

623
00:43:11,460 --> 00:43:12,320
Yes.

624
00:43:17,890 --> 00:43:18,470
It's funny, isn't it?

625
00:43:19,190 --> 00:43:20,490
A gisaeng meeting a beggar.

626
00:43:21,750 --> 00:43:22,830
No.

627
00:43:23,650 --> 00:43:24,530
What's so funny about it?

628
00:43:25,130 --> 00:43:27,130
Can you understand?

629
00:43:29,310 --> 00:43:30,470
Of course.

630
00:43:31,030 --> 00:43:36,770
If it's true love, it doesn't matter what the man does for a living.

631
00:43:38,090 --> 00:43:41,650
But it is a bit special.

632
00:43:43,630 --> 00:43:46,230
That Anchovy punk is finished.

633
00:43:46,790 --> 00:43:49,730
With the police all over the place, it's only a matter of time before he's caught, right?

634
00:43:50,470 --> 00:43:53,130
You're going to get a windfall without even lifting a finger, sir.

635
00:43:53,130 --> 00:43:56,510
The police are going to take care of that thorn in your side, Anchovy.

636
00:43:58,970 --> 00:44:01,470
I thought you would be happy, sir.

637
00:44:03,470 --> 00:44:04,070
What do you mean?

638
00:44:04,830 --> 00:44:09,550
You hated Anchovy so much that you were always waiting for something bad to happen to him.

639
00:44:12,230 --> 00:44:13,030
Why would I?

640
00:44:21,650 --> 00:44:23,890
You really don't understand people, do you?

641
00:44:25,070 --> 00:44:29,350
I'm the kind of person who hates getting things without working for them.

642
00:44:31,130 --> 00:44:32,490
Look at that samurai Chan-chan.

643
00:44:32,550 --> 00:44:33,590
Have you seen the movie or not?

644
00:44:34,410 --> 00:44:39,130
He carried a knife in his heart for over 10 years to get revenge.

645
00:44:41,630 --> 00:44:42,970
That guy.

646
00:44:43,350 --> 00:44:46,210
If he gets taken down by someone else right in front of my eyes, how would I feel?

647
00:44:47,090 --> 00:44:48,250
Then what should we do?

648
00:44:50,050 --> 00:44:51,870
Whatever happens.

649
00:44:52,530 --> 00:44:55,690
You have to find that guy before the police do.

650
00:44:55,930 --> 00:44:56,690
Got it?

651
00:45:14,830 --> 00:45:15,830
Sir.

652
00:45:27,060 --> 00:45:28,600
Don't look, don't look.

653
00:45:29,320 --> 00:45:30,380
Don't look.

654
00:45:33,950 --> 00:45:35,470
Are you really sure?

655
00:45:35,970 --> 00:45:36,890
There's no doubt about it.

656
00:45:37,670 --> 00:45:39,610
I'm telling you, a cop is definitely following us.

657
00:45:40,950 --> 00:45:41,530
Hey.

658
00:45:42,370 --> 00:45:44,390
Don't cops have anything better to do?

659
00:45:44,610 --> 00:45:46,110
Following around good citizens like us.

660
00:45:47,090 --> 00:45:49,150
Where the hell is that Chunsam hiding?

661
00:46:02,060 --> 00:46:04,100
What's so great that they're making such a fuss?

662
00:46:04,740 --> 00:46:05,860
That's just how it is.

663
00:46:06,700 --> 00:46:08,880
Does the outside world cry and laugh according to your mood?

664
00:46:09,880 --> 00:46:13,180
They don't have to, but that's what friends do.

665
00:46:14,200 --> 00:46:14,780
Du-han.

666
00:46:15,100 --> 00:46:17,140
Don't act so righteous all by yourself.

667
00:46:17,360 --> 00:46:18,740
I'm sad about Chunsam too.

668
00:46:19,740 --> 00:46:20,260
Sigh.

669
00:46:20,440 --> 00:46:22,560
Since when have you ever worried about us?

670
00:46:23,000 --> 00:46:23,220
Hey.

671
00:46:23,960 --> 00:46:25,180
You're talking about the past, right?

672
00:46:25,460 --> 00:46:26,700
Back when you were kids.

673
00:46:26,780 --> 00:46:30,720
That Pungmidang chrysanthemum bread I used to buy you every day during those hard times.

674
00:46:30,980 --> 00:46:32,540
Don't you remember eating that for several meals?

675
00:46:32,980 --> 00:46:34,660
I want to throw up all that chrysanthemum bread.

676
00:46:35,520 --> 00:46:36,300
Hey, you really.

677
00:46:36,500 --> 00:46:36,800
Sir, sir.

678
00:46:39,160 --> 00:46:39,680
Sir.

679
00:46:39,740 --> 00:46:39,740
Sir.

680
00:46:39,840 --> 00:46:39,840
Sir.

681
00:46:39,880 --> 00:46:40,100
Sir.

682
00:46:40,240 --> 00:46:40,240
Sir.

683
00:46:40,340 --> 00:46:40,340
Sir.

684
00:46:40,340 --> 00:46:40,340
Sir.

685
00:46:40,460 --> 00:46:40,720
Ah, why.

686
00:46:40,840 --> 00:46:40,840
Why.

687
00:46:40,940 --> 00:46:40,940
Why.

688
00:46:41,560 --> 00:46:42,520
You just got here, why?

689
00:47:03,690 --> 00:47:05,690
Give me an answer before you start drinking.

690
00:47:06,170 --> 00:47:08,650
No one is coming in here.

691
00:47:08,870 --> 00:47:08,990
Yes.

692
00:47:09,570 --> 00:47:09,570
Yes.

693
00:47:09,690 --> 00:47:09,770
Yes.

694
00:47:09,770 --> 00:47:10,050
Go upstairs.

695
00:47:10,450 --> 00:47:11,050
Here.

696
00:47:12,010 --> 00:47:12,610
Here.

697
00:47:16,080 --> 00:47:16,460
Here?

698
00:47:20,980 --> 00:47:21,580
Hyeongdo.

699
00:47:22,040 --> 00:47:22,460
Hyeongdo.

700
00:47:24,700 --> 00:47:25,300
Chunsam.

701
00:47:26,300 --> 00:47:26,540
Wow.

702
00:47:26,840 --> 00:47:29,460
Isn't something happening at Yeomcheon Bridge because of me?

703
00:47:29,900 --> 00:47:30,160
What?

704
00:47:30,320 --> 00:47:30,920
Why are you here?

705
00:47:30,920 --> 00:47:32,120
That...

706
00:47:32,400 --> 00:47:33,960
Yeomcheon Bridge is already...

707
00:47:34,380 --> 00:47:37,300
a mess, and two beggars have been arrested by the police.

708
00:47:37,580 --> 00:47:38,260
Who?

709
00:47:38,420 --> 00:47:38,540
Who?

710
00:47:38,700 --> 00:47:38,820
Who?

711
00:47:39,900 --> 00:47:40,900
Parrot and Fly.

712
00:47:41,040 --> 00:47:41,560
Fly too?

713
00:47:42,700 --> 00:47:43,980
He's not even healthy.

714
00:47:44,460 --> 00:47:47,300
They're homeless, so who knows how they'll be treated.

715
00:47:47,520 --> 00:47:48,860
They must be in a terrible state by now.

716
00:48:05,220 --> 00:48:05,940
Dokkae.

717
00:48:06,860 --> 00:48:07,280
Yes, sir.

718
00:48:08,140 --> 00:48:10,540
I smell a rotten stench coming from somewhere.

719
00:48:10,700 --> 00:48:10,880
How about it?

720
00:48:13,640 --> 00:48:14,320
Hey.

721
00:48:14,520 --> 00:48:15,060
He's my brother.

722
00:48:15,200 --> 00:48:15,360
Wait a minute.

723
00:48:19,180 --> 00:48:19,860
Wow.

724
00:48:20,200 --> 00:48:22,400
A runaway is living better than me.

725
00:48:22,880 --> 00:48:24,880
Sitting pretty in a bathtub.

726
00:48:26,180 --> 00:48:26,480
Hey.

727
00:48:26,540 --> 00:48:26,940
Where are you going?

728
00:48:28,660 --> 00:48:29,340
Where?

729
00:48:29,900 --> 00:48:30,400
I have to go.

730
00:48:30,580 --> 00:48:32,060
My kids are about to be beaten to death because of me.

731
00:48:33,260 --> 00:48:35,100
They'll suffer a bit, but they won't die.

732
00:48:35,580 --> 00:48:37,060
Still, I can't just leave them to get beaten.

733
00:48:38,620 --> 00:48:41,240
Walking into the police station on your own two feet is insane.

734
00:48:41,240 --> 00:48:44,260
They're innocent, so they'll get beaten a little and then released.

735
00:48:44,960 --> 00:48:49,680
But you'll be in prison until your hair turns white, or you'll become a target.

736
00:48:54,270 --> 00:48:56,150
Just hide here until tonight.

737
00:48:56,970 --> 00:48:58,910
And then leave for Incheon at dawn tomorrow.

738
00:48:59,430 --> 00:49:02,270
I'll find a boat that's smuggling people to Shanghai.

739
00:49:08,080 --> 00:49:09,180
Oh, that's right.

740
00:49:09,240 --> 00:49:09,540
Sir.

741
00:49:10,000 --> 00:49:12,360
Anchovy is going to Shanghai.

742
00:49:14,400 --> 00:49:18,720
I almost let him go, not knowing he was right under our noses.

743
00:49:19,760 --> 00:49:21,240
Dokkae, you go to the police station now.

744
00:49:21,900 --> 00:49:22,460
Yes, sir.

745
00:49:23,560 --> 00:49:23,920
No.

746
00:49:24,380 --> 00:49:26,000
Just keep a close watch so they don't escape.

747
00:49:26,880 --> 00:49:27,520
Yes, sir.

748
00:49:36,180 --> 00:49:36,800
Two.

749
00:49:45,320 --> 00:49:46,220
If you like it here, come in.

750
00:49:50,980 --> 00:49:52,240
Have you been keeping a good watch?

751
00:49:52,520 --> 00:49:52,940
Yes, sir.

752
00:49:53,360 --> 00:49:55,560
Du-han and the slippery one are gone, but that one hasn't moved an inch.

753
00:49:55,560 --> 00:49:55,740
Yes, sir.

754
00:49:55,960 --> 00:49:56,060
Sir.

755
00:49:56,120 --> 00:49:56,660
Did Du-han go?

756
00:49:57,020 --> 00:49:57,500
Yes, sir.

757
00:49:57,600 --> 00:49:57,900
Where?

758
00:49:58,980 --> 00:50:01,460
I'd appreciate it if you could give me a little time.

759
00:50:01,960 --> 00:50:09,260
Isn't it easier to catch a frog whose limbs are limp than one that's full of energy and jumping all over the place?

760
00:50:10,280 --> 00:50:10,820
And by the way.

761
00:50:11,360 --> 00:50:16,860
That guy and I go way back, so I have some things to sort out with him.

762
00:50:17,720 --> 00:50:19,800
It's fine to sort things out, but don't kill him.

763
00:50:20,340 --> 00:50:22,760
He still has a lot to confess.

764
00:50:23,140 --> 00:50:24,080
Don't you worry.

765
00:50:42,170 --> 00:50:43,030
Yes, sir.

766
00:50:43,030 --> 00:50:49,610
Either I die, or that guy dies, or we both die.

767
00:50:50,430 --> 00:50:53,770
You guys stay here and guard this place tight.

768
00:50:54,170 --> 00:50:58,850
And no matter what you hear, don't come in.

769
00:50:59,570 --> 00:51:00,010
Got it?

770
00:51:00,890 --> 00:51:01,270
Yes, sir.

771
00:51:24,660 --> 00:51:30,700
Tell them that Kim Chunsam, the Boss of Yeomcheon Bridge, got arrested for punching a Japanese guy.

772
00:51:32,140 --> 00:51:35,360
But that's not enough, so he's inciting the beggars!

773
00:51:35,920 --> 00:51:41,840
I want to live my life meeting Chunsam whenever I miss him, and holding his hand whenever I want to.

774
00:51:42,620 --> 00:51:44,180
That guy is going to prison.

775
00:51:45,420 --> 00:51:47,460
I'll do whatever you want.

776
00:51:48,050 --> 00:51:49,160
Are you from Yeomcheon Bridge?

777
00:51:50,740 --> 00:51:51,740
Not Chunsam.

778
00:51:52,440 --> 00:51:55,580
You have to endure it.

779
00:51:56,553 --> 00:51:59,593
A Joseon beggar lives by his guts and dies by his guts

